-- Putin Condemns Killing of U.S. Envoy in Libya, Interfax Says
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-09-13T16:45:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-13/putin-condemns-killing-of-u-s-envoy-in-libya-interfax-says.html
Russian President  Vladimir Putin 
condemned the killings of U.S diplomats including the ambassador
in Libya and offered his condolences to the families of those
who died, Interfax reported, citing comments made to reporters
in the Black Sea resort of Sochi.  The deaths should push countries to cooperate more closely
in fighting terrorism, he said today, according to the news
agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
 yfedorinova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
